 :tx/rationale "AUDIT-W4-003: Add test-result ingestion path to store cargo test outcomes as datoms. PROBLEM: bilateral.rs checks spec-impl alignment (boundary 3) but NOT impl-behavior alignment (boundary 4). cargo test results are consumed by CI but not by braid. INV-BILATERAL-005 requires test results stored as datoms. The Impl-Behavior boundary is completely unmonitored — test failures do not reduce F(S). SOLUTION: (1) Add braid test-import command that parses cargo test JSON output (cargo test -- --format json). (2) For each test: create entity with :test/name, :test/result (pass/fail/ignored), :test/file, :test/duration. (3) Link to spec via :test/verifies Ref to the spec entity if test name matches an INV pattern. (4) Wire into bilateral: backward_scan checks for test failures on linked impl entities. (5) F(S).V (Validation) component should incorporate test pass rate. VERIFICATION: (1) E2E: cargo test -- --format json | braid test-import produces datoms. (2) Unit test: failing test reduces F(S).V score. (3) braid status shows test coverage metric. DEPENDS-ON: None (new command). INTERACTS-WITH: W1-001 (F(S) weights include test coverage via Validation boundary)."
